Maya boolean operation works only when you know how to support maya with geo. 

Here is an example cutting a round shape in the center of a square. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

With round shape, we suggest to use 8 sides cylinder, it has geo easy to work with and when smoothed is round enough. 

Boolean operation can be modified after it is applied. In attribute editor, select the booleanOperation node, we can change the type of operation and intersection classification as well. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

When smoothed, we need to support the square edges, but not affecting the rounded shapes in the middle. Therefore, the bevel info must be contained in the flat area. 

First, we add two edge loops to contain the geo. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

We let the bevel geo info to go in one section, so the geo would not affect the square edge flow. 

Like this. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Then, we use multi-cut tool to fix the geo. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)
